IMMEDIATE
No.55/4/CF-67
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA
GABINET SECRETARIAT
(Department of Cabinet Affairs)
New Delhi, the 19th January, 1967.
---
The undersigned is directed to state that, with effeet
from the afternoon of Tuesday, January 17, 1967,
(i)
Shri S.K. Dey relinquished the office of
Minister of Mines & Metals; and
(11)
Shri T.N. Singh, Minister of Iron & Steel,
assumed charge temporarily of the Ministry
of Mines & Metals, in addition to his
charge of the Ministry of Iron & Steel..
( D.P. Chopra )
for Cabinet Secretary.
To
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
All Parliamentary Secretaries.
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the Prime Minister/
the Joint Secretary to the Prime Minister/the Private Secretary
to the Prime Minister, for information.
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the President/
Secretary to the Vice-President, for information.
the

Copy forwarded to all Ministries/Departments of the
Government of India/Lok Sabha Secretariat/Rajya Sabha

( D.P. Chopra )
